Fulcrum is distributed under two licences, split by component.

MODEL  ->  GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0)

    Covers everything except the user interface: the decision-architecture
    model and its supporting code. In the source tree that is fulcrum/domain,
    fulcrum/application, fulcrum/infrastructure and fulcrum/shared, together
    with main.py, the build scripts and the tests.
    Full text: LICENSE-GPL-3.0.txt

USER INTERFACE  ->  GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0 (LGPL-3.0)

    Covers the PySide6 and Qt layer (fulcrum/ui), licensed under the LGPL to
    align with Qt's own licensing. Full text: LICENSE-LGPL-3.0.txt, which
    incorporates the terms of the GPL-3.0 in LICENSE-GPL-3.0.txt.

The running application shows both under its Help menu: "Model licence
(GPL-3.0)" and "UI licence (LGPL-3.0)".

